    subcategory: 'Design & Innovation',
    definition: 'Design Thinking is a human-centered, iterative problem-solving methodology that emphasizes understanding user needs, challenging assumptions, redefining problems, and creating innovative solutions. The process typically involves five phases: Empathize understand users and their needs through observation and interviews, Define clearly articulate the problem based on insights gathered, Ideate generate a wide range of ideas through brainstorming and divergent thinking, Prototype create low-fidelity versions of solutions to test concepts quickly and cheaply, and Test gather feedback on prototypes and refine solutions. Design Thinking is non-linear teams cycle through phases as needed based on what they learn.',
