    whyItMatters: 'Design Thinking reduces the risk of building products nobody wants by putting user needs at the center of the process. It helps teams avoid the common trap of falling in love with their solution before validating the problem. It is used by companies like Apple, Google, and IDEO to create innovative products that genuinely improve people lives.',
